(# Multimodal Fusion Guide) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This document summarizes the current bundle priorities and fusion logic used by the screening runtime.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 1. Bundle Priorities) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The current runtime preference order is:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Text: text_transformer primary, text fallback) Tj
T*
(- Audio: audio primary, audio_spectrogram and audio_sequence secondary) Tj
T*
(- Image: image_dl primary, image fallback) Tj
T*
(- Comorbidity: classifier-chain ensemble blended with upstream text, audio, and image consensus) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(These priorities are intentional. The project keeps the strongest trained bundle in front for each modality and uses the other bundles as stabilizers or fallback signals.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 2. Why The Priorities Matter) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The system is designed to be robust in field use:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- strong modality bundles carry most of the final signal,) Tj
T*
(- auxiliary branches help when the primary bundle is uncertain,) Tj
T*
(- weaker bundle families do not overrule the stronger ones,) Tj
T*
(- the final score remains stable even when one modality is missing.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 3. Audio Fusion) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Audio uses:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- the main audio bundle as the primary scorer,) Tj
T*
(- audio_spectrogram as a secondary stabilizer,) Tj
T*
(- audio_sequence as a fallback stabilizer.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The runtime gives mood-heavy domains like depression, loneliness, anxiety, sleep disorder, and burnout slightly more room to move than the stronger substance-abuse domain.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 4. Image Fusion) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Image uses:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- image_dl as the primary scorer,) Tj
T*
(- the classical image bundle as a stabilizer.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The DL model gets a slightly higher influence when both are available.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 5. Text Fusion) Tj
ET
endstream
